<dl id="n25063k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25063k">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25063k"> 63(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hearth money </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: The Hearth Money Tax, levied on the number of hearths in a household, was introduced soon after the return of Charles II, as an instrument to extract payment for the Crown from the defeated Irish race. <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c14036i" href="c14all.htm#c14036i">VI.C.14:036(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
